data: Airbnb, Inc., together with its subsidiaries, operates a platform that enables hosts to offer stays and experiences to guests worldwide. Its marketplace connects hosts and guests online or through mobile devices to book spaces and experiences. It also offers gift cards. The company was formerly known as AirBed & Breakfast, Inc. and changed its name to Airbnb, Inc. in November 2010. Airbnb, Inc. was founded in 2007 and is headquartered in San Francisco, California.
In 2024, Airbnb's revenue was $11.10 billion, an increase of 11.95% compared to the previous year's $9.92 billion. Earnings were $2.65 billion, a decrease of -44.74%.
According to 31 analysts, the average rating for ABNB stock is "Hold." The 12-month stock price forecast is $147.26, which is an increase of 9.58% from the latest price.
